                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d80">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.34119/1270: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-26T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 26, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. For Braden. Your 69, March 25, 9 p.m. Mapa General de la Republica de Bolivia
                    (1934) shows a town called Ibibobo on the east bank of the Pilcomayo approximate
                    latitude 21º37″ south and longitude 62º55″ west. Argentine military maps may be
                    helpful if Conference has access to them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
